               <Label fx:id="csDescriptionLabel" layoutX="14.0" layoutY="37.0" text="Explores the principles underlying the design and implementation of modern computer systems with emphasis on operating systems. Fundamental topics in computer architecture and parallel/distributed computing are also covered. You will study Concurrency and Processes: Co-routines and processes. Synchronization. Scheduling, Resource management, Memory management: Address translation; TLBs. Segmentation and paging. Virtual memory, Device management: Device drivers. File systems. Access control; protection and authorization, and Networks and Distributed Systems: Communication protocols. Distributed file systems">
